{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory alcolocks for all drivers returning from drink-driving bans",
        "additional_details": "Drink-driving remains one of the leading causes of serious injuries and fatalities on UK roads. While existing sanctions remove offenders from the road temporarily, there\u2019s limited assurance that reoffending will not occur once they regain their license. \r\nStudies & trials (across several European nations) have shown that using alcolocks significantly reduces reoffending rates.",
        "background": "Drivers returning from a drink-drive ban must have an alcolock fitted to their vehicle as a licensing condition for a defined period (e.g. 24 months)\r\nPeriodic monitoring to ensure compliance\r\nGovernment funding & incentives are explored to support the installation & administration of this system",
